# cPanel Security Funtions

## IP Deny Manager

IP Deny Manager will allow you to block a range of IP addresses to prevent them from accessing your site. You can also enter a fully qualified domain name, and the IP Deny Manager will attempt to resolve it to an IP address for you.

IP Deny Manager can be access from the cPanel account.

- Login to cPanel Account
- Under Security click on IP Deny Manager

```diagram

```

- In the new page write the domain name /ip address you want to block and then click on Add

```diagram

```


## Password Protected Directories

This option will allow you to require a username and password to access a folder or folders from the web. This can be very useful when you need to limit access to a certain part of your site.

- Login to cPanel of your account
- Click on Password Protected Directories under Security

```diagram

```

- Then a list of the directories on your account will appear. 

```diagram

```

- Click on the directory you wish to limit access to. In the new page, please create a new username and a password.


```diagram

```

- Select a name that will appear in the login screen and select the option Password protect this directory: and click on the Save button to activate the protection.

```diagram

```


## Enable Leech Protection

Leech Protect allows you to prevent your users from giving out or publicly posting their password to a restricted area of your site. This feature will redirect (and suspend if selected) accounts which have been compromised to a url of your choice.

- Login to your cPanel account
- Click on Leech Protect under security.

```diagram

```

- Please select the folder you wish to protect by clicking on its name. You can navigate by clicking on icons.


```diagram

```

- On the next screen , Enter the required values and parameters accordingly and then click on Enable button.

```diagram

```
